item.title: 718 Teleport Commands
item.dc:creator: @Null_Amount N_A
item.description:
@Null_Amount wrote:

Good: switch (test) { case "example": if (blah) { //You can do this! } break; }
Bad: switch (test) { case "example": //blah break; if (blahBlah) { //This is bad, don't do this! } }
Alternatively, you could just look at the code. What looks different about your command that makes it differ from every other working command?

item.title: 718 Teleport Commands
item.dc:creator: @si_force Si Force
item.description:
@si_force wrote:

Can you try and read what they are saying to you? You are trying to add an if-statement into a switch statement, which cannot be done unless declared in a case. (the cause of your error)

Take the other command examples around that and then try and implement the home command using a case. Example:

case "home":
	//teleport command here
	break;

What he is talking about is directly related to what you are trying to do.

http://docs.oracle.com/javase/tutorial/java/nutsandbolts/switch.html

[code=java]public class StringSwitchDemo {

public static int getMonthNumber(String month) {

    int monthNumber = 0;

    if (month == null) {
        return monthNumber;
    }

    switch (month.toLowerCase()) {
        case "january":
            monthNumber = 1;
            break;
        case "february":
            monthNumber = 2;
            break;
        case "march":
            monthNumber = 3;
            break;
        case "april":
            monthNumber = 4;
            break;
        case "may":
            monthNumber = 5;
            break;
        case "june":
            monthNumber = 6;
            break;
        case "july":
            monthNumber = 7;
            break;
        case "august":
            monthNumber = 8;
            break;
        case "september":
            monthNumber = 9;
            break;
        case "october":
            monthNumber = 10;
            break;
        case "november":
            monthNumber = 11;
            break;
        case "december":
            monthNumber = 12;
            break;
        default: 
            monthNumber = 0;
            break;
    }

    return monthNumber;
